page.title: 12Housing 2
page.content: Barnet Road and Wood Street are mostly housing but there are one or two farms. The most biggest of them all is Whale Bone Farm which is on the south side of Wood Street. It starts more or less opposite Kings Road and stretches to the juction where Wood Street and Barnet Road meet. At the junction there is also a pub called Arkley. From there on the land use is mostly housing but at the corner of Field End there is the Arkley Mens Club. After that we came to Quinta Drive and after that to the Arkley racing stables. From there on there is a bit of grassland, some houses and then a church which used to be a school. There are some more grassland and then some shops which include a car dealer then its mostly housing to Barnet Gate.
